Method for preparing purified for the crystal methamphetamine standard substance of forensic science illicit drugs inspection

Abstract
translated from Chinese

The invention discloses a method for purifying and preparing methamphetamine standard substances used in forensic drug detection, comprising the following steps: (1) detecting the purity of methamphetamine in seized methamphetamine samples, and selecting methamphetamine with a mass fraction greater than or equal to 70wt % of the seized methamphetamine samples are used as raw materials for purification and preparation of methamphetamine standard substances; (2) high performance liquid chromatography is utilized to prepare methamphetamine standard substances; the resulting methamphetamine has high purity and can be directly used as standard substances. The methamphetamine obtained by the preparation and purification method of the present invention is confirmed by nuclear magnetic resonance, liquid chromatography-tandem mass spectrometry, and infrared spectrum analysis, and its purity is determined by liquid chromatography and gas chromatography, and the chromatographic non-responsive impurities are measured; According to the requirements for the development of reference materials, the estimation of its stability, uniformity, fixed value, and total uncertainty all meet the relevant regulations and meet the expected indicators.

Description
translated from Chinese

Purification and preparation of methamphetamine standard substances for forensic drug testing method

technical field

The present invention relates to forensic science drug testing. More specifically, it relates to a method for purifying and preparing methamphetamine standard substances used in forensic drug detection.

Background technique

At present, the increasingly serious drug problem has become a global disaster. The proliferation of drugs directly endangers people's physical and mental health, and poses a huge threat to economic development and social progress. Therefore, establishing a forensic scientific drug detection quantity traceability system, improving the measurement technology of drug components, ensuring the reliability and comparability of measurement results, establishing the sharing and mutual recognition of measurement data, and providing accurate and reliable evidence for courts has become a national standard in the world. A general concern of drug identification agencies.

Drug composition measurement technology and traceability guarantee are an organic whole, which is an important embodiment of core measurement capabilities in the field of forensic drug composition measurement. The reference material is the skeleton that runs through the whole, the carrier of the quantity value, the key element of the traceability system of drug ingredients, the important basis for ensuring the accuracy and comparability of the measurement results in time and space, and the realization of effective measurement that is The fundamental guarantee for accurate, comparable and traceable measurements.

SigmaMost of the advanced drug testing laboratories in Europe and the United States use internationally recognized reference materials produced by companies such as Sigma, but in my country we can only rely on imported reference materials, which are small in quantity and high in price, and many of them cannot be provided to China. At present, the types of "reference substances" used in domestic drug analysis are not only extremely limited, but also generally lack corresponding technical indicators such as perfect structure identification, purity determination, uniformity and stability. All of these bring certain uncertainties to the detection of drug-related cases and directly affect the accuracy of quantitative results. Moreover, the lack of domestic drug standard substances has become a major obstacle restricting my country from realizing the standardization of forensic drug detection chemical measurement methods, traceability and mutual recognition of measurement results. Therefore, the ability to prepare drug reference substances for forensic drug detection has become an urgent problem in the field of drug research in my country.

Methamphetamine hydrochloride1--2-Chemical NameDimethylphenylethylamine hydrochlorideCHNHCl185.70(anhyd.)CA51-57-0Methamphetamine is also known as methamphetamine, methamphetamine, methamphetamine, methamphetamine. English common name: Methamphetamine hydrochloride, chemical name: 1-phenyl-2-methylaminopropane, Chemical Name: Dimethylphenylethylamine hydrochloride, methamphetamine hydrochloride molecular formula: C 10 H 15 N HCl, molecular weight: 185.70 (anhyd.) , CA registration number: 51-57-0 The structural formula is:

172174(50mg/mL)Physical and chemical properties: slightly bitter taste, is a colorless flaky crystal, melting point 172 ~ 174 , soluble in water (50mg/mL), ethanol, insoluble in ether, free base has ammonia odor. Due to the presence of a chiral carbon atom in the methamphetamine molecule, methamphetamine is further divided into a left-handed optical isomer and a right-handed optical isomer, and an equal mixture of the two forms a racemate. The optical structure is different, and its medicinal effect is very different. According to the literature, D-methamphetamine is several times higher than L-methamphetamine.

Contents of the invention

The object of the present invention is to provide a kind of method for the purification and preparation of methamphetamine standard substance used for forensic science drug detection.

To achieve the above object, the present invention adopts the following technical solutions:

The preparation method for the purification of the methamphetamine standard substance that is used for forensic science drug detection comprises the steps:

(1)70wt(1) detect and seize the purity of methamphetamine in the methamphetamine sample, select the methamphetamine mass fraction greater than or equal to 70wt% and seize the methamphetamine sample as the raw material for purification and preparation of methamphetamine standard substance;

(2)(2) Utilize high-performance liquid chromatography to prepare methamphetamine standard substance.

(1)The above-mentioned purification preparation method for the methamphetamine standard substance that is used for forensic science drug detection, in step (1), comprises the following steps:

(1.1)1mg1mL1mg/mL0.45m(1.1) Preparation of sample solution: Weigh 1 mg of methamphetamine sample and dissolve it in 1 mL of methanol to form a mass volume concentration of 1 mg/mL methamphetamine sample solution for HPLC analysis. Before use, the sample solution is subjected to 0.45 m microporous membrane filtration.

(1.2)Shim-pack HRC-ODS(250mm4.6mm I.D.5m)0.05/25:75220nm1.0mL/min(1.2) Determine the liquid chromatography conditions: the chromatographic column is a Shim-pack HRC-ODS column (250mm4.6mm I.D., 5 m); the mobile phase is methanol: 0.05% trifluoroacetic acid/water=25:75, isocratic elution ; UV detection wavelength 220nm; flow rate 1.0mL/min; column temperature is room temperature;

(1.3)1.0mg/mL1.0,0.5,0.1,0.05,0.01,0.005,0.001mg/mL(1.2)3(g/mL)Y1930+510CR1.00000.0011mg/mL(1.3) Calculate the regression equation of the standard curve and determine the linear range: dilute the commercially available 1.0 mg/mL methamphetamine methanol solution step by step with chromatographic methanol, and prepare the concentrations as 1.0, 0.5, 0.1, 0.05, 0.01, 0.005, 0.001 The methamphetamine standard solution of mg/mL is determined by the chromatographic conditions selected in step (1.2), each concentration is repeated 3 times, calculated as the average value, and the methamphetamine chromatographic peak area is recorded, and the injection concentration of the standard (g/mL) is the abscissa, and the chromatographic peak area value is plotted on the ordinate, and the regression equation of the standard curve is calculated. The regression equation of the standard curve is: Y=1930+510 6 C, R 2 =1.0000; determine Linear range: methamphetamine has a good linear relationship within the range of 0.001-1mg/mL;

(1.4)10mg10mL1mg/mL0.45mHPLC3(1.4) Accurately weigh 10 mg of methamphetamine white crystal sample in a 10 mL volumetric flask, dilute to volume with chromatographic methanol and mix well to prepare a sample solution with a mass concentration of 1 mg/mL; take the solution and pass it through a 0.45 m microporous membrane After filtration, carry out HPLC analysis, measure 3 times continuously, record methamphetamine peak area and calculate its average value, calculate the content of methamphetamine in the sample according to peak area external standard method.

(2)The above-mentioned purification preparation method for the methamphetamine standard substance that is used for forensic science drug detection, in step (2), comprises the following steps:

(2.1)640mg2mL/(1:1)5min320mg/mL0.45m(2.1) Preparation of sample solution: 640mg methamphetamine sample was placed in a 2mL volumetric flask, methanol/water (volume ratio 1:1) was added to the scale line, ultrasonicated for 5min until the sample was completely dissolved, and prepared into 320mg/mL formazan The sample solution of methamphetamine was used for preparative high performance liquid chromatography to prepare methamphetamine standard. (2.3)pH122110.01NHClpH4-5(2.3) The collected cuts are obtained by rotary evaporation under reduced pressure to obtain colorless transparent crystals, which are dissolved in distilled water and adjusted to a pH of 12; add n-hexane and extract 2 times, and the volume ratio of the aqueous phase to the organic phase during each extraction is 1:1, combine the organic phase, add 1/2 of the volume of the organic phase to the organic phase, add 0.01N HCl solution drop by drop until the pH of the solution is 4-5, remove n-hexane by rotary evaporation, and freeze the remaining water phase Drying or rotary evaporation obtains crystals of the final product methamphetamine hydrochloride, which are placed in a vacuum drying oven to dry at room temperature.

(2.1)Above-mentioned purification preparation method for the methamphetamine standard substance that is used for forensic science drug detection, in step (2.1), at first the methamphetamine sample is carried out chiral analysis, and selects the sample that only contains single isomer configuration as preparation The starting material was obtained from the corresponding isomer standard material.

The beneficial effects of the present invention are as follows:

99.1wtIn the methamphetamine crystal obtained by the preparation and purification method of the present invention, the purity of the methamphetamine calculated according to the peak area normalization method of high performance liquid chromatography is greater than or equal to 99.1 wt%.

-The methamphetamine obtained by the preparation and purification method of the present invention is confirmed by nuclear magnetic resonance, liquid chromatography-tandem mass spectrometry, and infrared spectrum analysis, and its purity is determined by liquid chromatography and gas chromatography, and the chromatographic non-responsive impurities are measured; According to the requirements for the development of reference materials, the estimation of its stability, uniformity, fixed value, and total uncertainty all meet the relevant regulations and meet the expected indicators.

The preparation and purification method of the present invention can provide my country's judicial appraisal department with accurate and traceable methamphetamine standard substances, fill the blank of drug standard substances in the field of forensic science in my country, improve the quality of analysis and measurement, and improve the accuracy of quantitative results. To ensure the validity of the measurement results to the greatest extent. It is helpful to establish a traceability system for forensic science drug detection quantity, is conducive to the standardization of domestic forensic science drug detection chemical measurement methods, and realizes the reliability, effectiveness and mutual recognition of measurement results.

It overcomes the defects of low purity, poor stability, poor uniformity, and complicated preparation process in the methamphetamine samples obtained by the preparation and purification methods of the prior art, and provides a high-purity, high-stability, high-performance liquid chromatography separation method. The invention discloses a method for preparing methamphetamine standard substance which has high recovery rate and is convenient for large-scale production.

2.5R(-)-S(+)-2.5 Selection of raw materials for the preparation of R(-)-methamphetamine and S(+)-methamphetamine standard substances

In principle, during the liquid chromatography separation process for the preparation of methamphetamine, if no chiral derivatization reagent or chiral catalyst is added, the entire preparation process will not lead to changes in the spatial configuration of isomers. Therefore, according to the chiral analysis results of the crystals seized in the case, we can choose crystal samples containing only a single isomer configuration as raw materials for preparation to obtain corresponding isomer standard substances.

R(-)-methamphetamineS(+)-methamphetamineAccording to the measurement results of the samples seized in the case, crystal samples containing only R(-)-methamphetamine and S(+)-methamphetamine were selected and prepared into sample solutions respectively, and different chiral methamphetamines could be obtained by preparative liquid chromatography separation optical isomers.

3.43.4 Optimization of HPLC analysis conditions

3.4.13.4.1 Selection of chromatographic column

HPLCCshim-pack HRC-ODS(250mm4.6mmI.D.5m)According to bibliographical reports, the HPLC analysis of methamphetamine sample adopts the reversed-phase high-performance liquid chromatography method more, utilizes C 18 chromatographic column to analyze. Since the HPLC analysis method established in the experiment should not only be suitable for the analysis of methamphetamine crystal samples, but also be conducive to the later scale-up and establishment of the HPLC preparation method, the selection of the chromatographic column comprehensively considered the column packing, corresponding Preparative column model, price and other factors, using shim-pack HRC-ODS (250mm4.6mmI.D., 5m) analytical chromatographic column to analyze methamphetamine samples.

Acetic acid aqueous solution) is the mobile phase, the loading volume is 10 L, the sample concentration is 1 mg/mL, the flow rate is 1.0 mL/min, the temperature is room temperature, and the detection wavelengths are respectively 210 nm, 215 nm, 220 nm, 230 nm, 235 nm, 254 nm, and p-methamphetamine sample solution HPLC analysis was performed. 6220nm254nm210nm215nm230nm235nm200220nm(2)220nmAccording to the test results, under the selected 6 wavelength conditions, at 220nm, the detected impurity components are the most, and the response of each impurity component is higher, followed by 254nm, 210nm, 215nm, and under the conditions of 230nm and 235nm Impurities have the lowest response. Combined with methamphetamine's maximum ultraviolet absorption range of 200-220nm (Figure 2), the detection wavelength of the determination method is 220nm.

3.4.33.4.3 Selection of mobile phase system

220nm-0.05(TFA)/-0.5/(0.5/0.5)---0.05(TFA)/In reversed-phase bonded phase chromatography, water is usually used as the main mobile phase, and methanol, acetonitrile or tetrahydrofuran are added as modifiers to improve the selectivity of separation. Since the ultraviolet absorption wavelength of tetrahydrofuran is 220nm, which is the same as the detection wavelength selected by the test, in order to avoid the background interference caused by the mobile phase, regarding the selection of the reversed-phase liquid chromatography mobile phase system, methanol-0.05% trifluoroacetic acid (TFA) /water system, methanol-0.5% acetic acid/water system (0.5% acetic acid/water refers to the acetic acid aqueous solution whose volume fraction of acetic acid is 0.5%), methanol-water system, acetonitrile-water system and acetonitrile-0.05% trifluoroacetic acid (TFA )/water system was investigated.

-0.05(TFA)/Alcohol-0.05% trifluoroacetic acid (TFA)/water system investigation

10L1mg/mL1.0mL/min220nm1520253035-0.05The sample volume is 10 L, the sample concentration is 1 mg/mL, the temperature is room temperature, the flow rate is 1.0 mL/min, and the detection wavelength is 220 nm. Trifluoroacetic acid aqueous solution was used as the mobile phase, and the separation of methamphetamine and its adjacent impurity peaks in the sample was investigated at different methanol ratios.

1520(34)40min30351530(6)35(7)25(5)30min-0.05(TFA)/25Know by experiment, along with the gradual increase of methanol content, mobile phase polarity reduces, and the retention time of each impurity peak and methamphetamine advances gradually. When methanol volume content is 15% and 20% (Fig. 3, Fig. 4), although adjacent impurity peak has reached baseline separation with methamphetamine chromatographic peak, analysis time is longer, surpassed 40min. During 30% and 35% methyl alcohol content, within 15 minutes, all components were eluted, methamphetamine and its front impurity peak reached baseline separation, but when methanol content was 30%, methylamine and its back impurity peak partially overlapped ( Fig. 6), when the methanol content is 35%, the impurity peak behind forms a shoulder peak (Fig. 7) on the methylamine chromatographic peak. When the methanol content was 25% (Fig. 5), all the components were washed out from the chromatographic column within 30 min, and the methylamine chromatographic peaks were separated from the front and rear impurity peaks by the baseline. Therefore, judge from test result, adopt methanol-0.05% trifluoroacetic acid (TFA)/water system to analyze methamphetamine sample solution, when 25% volume fraction methanol content, the separating effect of main component methamphetamine and adjacent impurity component is the best good.

The separation effect of the methanol-water system is significantly lower than that of the methanol-0.05% trifluoroacetic acid/water system.

Theoretically, the flow rate of the preparative chromatographic column can be linearly scaled up according to the following formula when the condition of analytical liquid chromatography is converted to the condition of preparative liquid chromatography with the same filler and the same column length.

Xr /r Xr 2 2 /r 1 2

X----Among them, X---magnification factor

r----r 2 ---- preparation column radius

r----r 1 ---- analysis column radius

4.6mm20mm18.918.9mL/min(20KPa)In this test, the radius of the analytical column is 4.6 mm, and the radius of the preparative column is 20 mm. If calculated according to the above formula, the amplification factor is 18.9, and the theoretically calculated flow rate of the preparative column is 18.9 mL/min. However, in the establishment of the separation method of preparative chromatography, if the flow rate is set according to the theoretical calculation value, the pressure of the chromatographic column will far exceed the maximum pressure (20KPa) limit, so the flow rate of the mobile phase is determined as follows through experimental investigation.

HPLC320mg/mL-0.5/(2575)-(5:95)75mAuUsually the preparation of liquid chromatography is carried out under the condition of column overloading. According to literature reports, in practical applications, when the same amount of sample is loaded, volume overloading has a greater impact on preparative separation column efficiency than mass overloading. Therefore, in preparative HPLC In general, the method of mass overloading is adopted. The concentration of the sample in this test is 320mg/mL, which is close to the saturated state of sample dissolution at room temperature. The separation conditions are methanol-0.5% acetic acid/water (both volume ratio 25:75) system or methanol-water (both volume ratio 5 : 95) water system is used as mobile phase, begins to collect cut from threshold greater than 75mAu, and cut is detected through analytical liquid chromatography. 3.4.6.43.4.6.4 Determination of fraction collection range

60mAu70mAu75mAu80mAu85mAuHPLC60mAu99.5wt75mAuUsing preparative liquid chromatography for separation and purification, fractions can be collected according to retention time, or according to threshold or chromatographic peak slope. Considering that the retention time of each injection is difficult to completely overlap, in order to avoid the introduction of impurities due to slight changes in retention time, the method of collecting fractions according to the signal threshold was adopted in the experiment, and the threshold values were higher than 60mAu, 70mAu, 75mAu, 80mAu, 85mAu respectively Fractions were collected within the range for HPLC analysis, and the results showed that fractions with a purity greater than 99.5wt% could be collected when the threshold was higher than 60mAu. Final determination was made to collect fractions with a signal threshold above the range of 75mAu.

3.4.6.53.4.6.5 Batch programs

45minAB(5:95)After testing and investigation, under the preparative liquid chromatographic conditions adopted, all components can flow out of the preparative column within 45 minutes. Therefore, in the batch operation process, we first use methanol and water in the mobile phase to pass through A and B respectively. After the pump is injected, it is mixed into the column through the preparation liquid phase. The separation effect was good at the beginning of the batch operation, but later it was found that the chromatographic peaks were seriously deformed, the retention time changed, and the instrument could not collect fractions according to the preset parameters. After searching the reason, it was found that the separation effect was caused by a large number of bubbles in the pipeline. caused by the decrease. Further tests have found that since the mobile phase system for preparing separation is composed of methanol and water, when water and methanol are mixed, exothermic phenomenon will occur, the volume of the mixed solvent will decrease, and a large number of bubbles will be released simultaneously. Therefore, the test uses methanol and water (the volume ratio of the two is 5:95) to be mixed in proportion before entering the pump, and then used after fully mixing and degassing. Batch runs allow for continuous injection.

3.4.6.63.4.6.6 Further purification of the methamphetamine fraction

pHpH12112100The automatic fraction collector collects the methamphetamine components after liquid phase separation, and obtains colorless transparent crystals after rotary evaporation under reduced pressure. Infrared spectroscopy can usually be used to detect whether the obtained transparent crystals are methamphetamine hydrochloride. It can also be further purified to obtain the final product methamphetamine hydrochloride. The method of solvent extraction was adopted in the experiment, and factors such as pH value, extraction solvent, extraction solvent dosage and extraction times were investigated respectively. The results showed that when the pH value was greater than 12, the extraction with n-hexane, the volume ratio of the aqueous phase to the organic phase was 1:1 in each extraction, and the recovery rate of the second extraction was close to 100%.

If it is greater than 12, add 1 mL of n-hexane for extraction, shake for 5 minutes, let stand to separate and separate, remove the organic phase, and analyze the remaining aqueous phase by HPLC, and calculate the extraction recovery under different pH conditions.

Under alkaline conditions, methamphetamine exists in its free form. With the increase of pH value, the extraction efficiency of n-hexane increases continuously. When the pH value is greater than 12, the extraction efficiency is the highest, reaching 91.67%. Therefore, it is determined that the optimum extraction pH value is greater than 12.

3.4.6.6.43.4.6.6.4 Determination of adding amount of hydrochloric acid solution

The methamphetamine obtained after extraction with n-hexane exists in the n-hexane solution in its original form, and further tests are required to obtain the final product methamphetamine hydrochloride. The test adopts the method of adding hydrochloric acid solution dropwise to n-hexane solution, and the addition amount of hydrochloric acid solution is investigated.

5mL,pH125mL10min5min5mL5mL0.01NHClCollect fractions from single-needle injection, remove the mobile phase by rotary evaporation, dissolve the residue with distilled water to 5mL, adjust the pH value of the solution to greater than 12, add 5mL of n-hexane, shake for 10min, centrifuge for 5min, remove the organic phase, and pour into the water phase Add 5 mL of n-hexane again for secondary extraction, combine the extracted n-hexane solutions twice, and add 5 mL of water to it, then add 0.01N HCl solution dropwise, and record the amount of hydrochloric acid solution by subtraction method.

2mL0.01NHClpH45,Experiments have shown that for the fraction collected by single-needle injection, after extraction with n-hexane, adding 2mL of 0.01N HCl solution, the pH value of the aqueous phase can reach 4-5, and the final product methamphetamine hydrochloride aqueous solution is obtained.

3.4.6.6.53.4.6.6.5 Drying of prepared products

After the distillate is extracted with n-hexane and further converted into methamphetamine hydrochloride, the n-hexane can be removed by rotary evaporation, and the remaining water phase can be freeze-dried or rotary-evaporated to obtain crystals of the final product methamphetamine hydrochloride. However, experiments have shown that impurities are easily introduced during the heating process of rotary evaporation, which reduces the purity of standard substances. Therefore, in order to obtain high-purity standard substances, freeze-drying technology should be used to obtain the final preparation. Simultaneously, experiments also found that when the hydrochloric acid solution was added in excess, the color of the final prepared product obtained after drying was yellowish.

The methamphetamine standard substance obtained after freeze-drying usually needs to be dehydrated to remove moisture and residual solvents adsorbed from the air. Although methamphetamine hydrochloride has good thermal stability, the dehydration and desolventization of the standard substance uses a vacuum drying oven. Dry at room temperature.
